I used PHPExcel 1.7.9 to output in PHPExcel5 format, here's an example. 

$objPHPExcel = new PHPExcel();
$objWriter = new PHPExcel_Writer_Excel5($objPHPExcel);
$objPHPExcel->getActiveSheet()->setCellValue("A1", "Col A");
$objPHPExcel->getActiveSheet()->setCellValue("A2", "Data A");
$objPHPExcel->getActiveSheet()->setCellValue("B1", "Col B");
$objPHPExcel->getActiveSheet()->setCellValue("B2", "Data B");
$objWriter->save("output.xls");

When I attempt to use the ODBC driver to run a query against the excel spreadsheet, the first column is missing.

Steps to reproduce:
Load Microsoft Excel 2010, choose Data..From Other Sources..From Microsoft Query
In Databases tab, choose Excel Files, find the generated output.xls and select it
In the Query Wizard, expand Worksheet$, Col A will not be present.

If you load the output.xls in Excel itself and do nothing except save it, everything does work fine.

